article.headline: Smith scores career-high 23 points
article.linkText: Reserve power: Smith lifts DePaul to win
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) --  Reserve Khara Smith scored a career-high 23
points, and Jenni Dant added 19 as  DePaul (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) defeated
Alabama-Birmingham 78-62 Friday night.

	   DePaul (13-4, 2-0 Conference USA) went on a 17-7 run in the
first half led by Smith, who scored 12 points during the span. The
Blue Demons held a 36-26 lead at halftime.

	   Smith, who was 11-of-14 from the floor, single-handedly
outscored UAB (5-10, 1-1) 8-4 during a three-minute stretch in the
second half. She also finished with nine rebounds.

	   Ashley Luke added 17 points for DePaul.

	   The Blazers were led by Michelle Smith's 23 points and 12
rebounds. Natasha Thomas added 20 points.

	   The Blue Demons outrebounded UAB 38-36, and shot 51.7 percent
from the field. The Blazers made 40 percent of their shots.

	   DePaul improved to a perfect 8-0 record at home and won for the
sixth time in seven games.
